just_use main.go

# label: SPRAWLING
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Compiler: .claude DSL pages → views/*.go handler source. Opt-in (only
files named on the CLI are compiled), so deleting a .claude and keeping
the .go unsticks a page from the pipeline without drama.

Generated .go files register themselves via init() → registerGeneratedPage
(see views/registry_generated.go). That's why a new DSL page needs no
edit to main.go or registry.go — just add the .claude, run crudgen,
commit both.

AST is deliberately flat (page → views → forms/tables/sections →
renderers). text/template does the rendering; golang.org/x/tools/imports
+ go/format enforce buildable output. This is the "trust multi-layer
codegen" principle in action (see memory feedback_trust_codegen_layers).
